Diagnosis . Female : usually micropterous (
Fig. 8
), occasionally brachypterous; head with dorsal side flat; maxillary palpi 3 - or 5 -segmented; labial palpi 2 -segmented; third segment of maxillary palpi broadened; ocelli absent or much reduced; first antenna geniculated; antennal segment much longer than segment 3 ; pronotum without or with track of median longitudinal furrow; scutellum subcircular; metanotum short and transverse; tibial spurs 1 / 2 / 2 . Male : fully winged (
Fig. 11
); fore wing usually with CC, BC, SBC, 1 DC cells enclosed by pigmented veins; 1 SDC cell open; 1 DC cell occasionally open; maxillary palpi 4 - or 6 -segmented; labial palpi 2 - or 3 - segmented; third segment of maxillary palpi broadened; region of face from clypeus to antennal toruli with two very convergent longitudinal and median sutures; ocelli distinct; head with dorsal side swollen; antenna not geniculated; first antennal segment shorter or slightly longer than segment 3 ; tibial spurs 1 / 2 / 2 .
